    "Body": " Compliance Program Manager OKCoin - San Francisco, CA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $69,000 - $98,000 a year Qualifications Communication Skills Management Experience Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Company A unique and highly-impactful role at one of the fastest-growing global cryptocurrency exchanges based in SF-SOMA (with stunning views of the Bay Bridge). We are looking for a seasoned compliance professional to provide strong compliance experience and central management for our compliance program globally including, but not limited to policies & procedures, exams, issue management, training and governance. The Compliance Program Manager will support the Global Chief Compliance Officer and complement our AML Officers located in the US, Europe and Asia to provide support and oversight for our global compliance program. Ideally this candidate will be located in the Bay Area, however we are also willing to accept candidates from Europe to be based in our office in Gzira, Malta. Job Functions In this role, you'll get to: Manage our global regulatory compliance program and implement company-wide regulatory compliance initiatives with support from the Global Chief Compliance Officer. Document and maintain all Compliance policies and procedures to ensure compliance with internal standards and all applicable laws and regulations , as well as maintain consistency globally Contribute to the continuous evolution of the end-to-end Compliance Program, including the framework, all policies and procedures, risk assessments, issue management and training Research local payments and digital asset regulations throughout Europe, Asia, and the Americas to ensure that our control environment complies with all local regulations where we operate Provide central coordination, working closely with the broader compliance team and international AML Officers to prepare for and execute AML audits and regulatory exams globally Develop and deliver training and communications on compliance policies and procedures to ensure proper understanding across the organization of regulatory related risks and responsibilities Provide compliance subject matter expertise cross-functionally and contribute to building a strong culture of compliance at OKCoin globally Prepare compliance presentation materials for quarterly board meetings and progress reports to the COO and CEO Travel to international OKCoin offices may be required On the first day, we'll expect you to have: Bachelor's Degree 10+ years of relevant AML compliance experience with a specific focus on financial services, fintech or virtual currency The ability to work efficiently and independently in an ambiguous, fast-paced environment, with a strong understanding of when to escalate urgent issues Strong interest in virtual currency or blockchain (prior experience preferred but not required) Experience implementing and managing compliance programs for a global financial services or fintech company Previous people management experience and the ability to influence others Excellent communication and presentation skills both verbal and written and at all organizational levels Fluency in Chinese-Mandarin a plus, but not required OKCoin Statement: OKCoin is committed to equal employment opportunities regardless of race, color, genetic information, creed, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, lawful alien status, national origin, age, marital status, and non-job related physical or mental disability, or protected veteran status. ", 
